347
00:18:58,920 --> 00:18:59,720
Alright then.

348
00:18:59,799 --> 00:19:00,960
I'll take these shrimp

349
00:19:00,960 --> 00:19:03,519
to the senior care kitchen.

350
00:19:03,559 --> 00:19:04,920
I'll thank you on their behalf.

351
00:19:04,960 --> 00:19:06,079
No need to thank me.

352
00:19:06,519 --> 00:19:08,799
I just asked you to help Li Zhenggui find a job this afternoon.

353
00:19:08,799 --> 00:19:10,079
And you found one by tonight.

354
00:19:10,079 --> 00:19:11,519
I should be thanking you.

355
00:19:11,599 --> 00:19:12,559
Did I play my part well?

356
00:19:12,559 --> 00:19:13,519
Did I give myself away?

357
00:19:14,400 --> 00:19:15,200
All good.

358
00:19:15,200 --> 00:19:16,160
Your place is really clean.

359
00:19:16,160 --> 00:19:17,359
You keep it spotless.

360
00:19:17,839 --> 00:19:19,440
Hope you keep up

361
00:19:19,440 --> 00:19:21,079
this spotless spirit.

362
00:19:21,079 --> 00:19:21,920
No need to see me out.

363
00:19:21,920 --> 00:19:23,279
I'm taking the shrimp now.

364
00:19:23,599 --> 00:19:25,079
Take care, Yu Dama.

365
00:19:31,400 --> 00:19:32,640
I guarded those shrimp all day,

366
00:19:32,640 --> 00:19:34,680
how could you just give them away?

367
00:19:35,599 --> 00:19:36,920
Sorry!

368
00:19:37,240 --> 00:19:38,480
Just think of it as

369
00:19:38,480 --> 00:19:40,519
a contribution to the senior care kitchen.

370
00:19:40,680 --> 00:19:41,839
Don't be mad.

371
00:19:42,480 --> 00:19:43,839
So what are we eating tonight?

372
00:19:43,839 --> 00:19:45,680
To celebrate your new job,

373
00:19:45,680 --> 00:19:47,359
we're having a feast tonight.

374
00:19:47,960 --> 00:19:50,000
Burgundy Beef Stew.

375
00:19:52,640 --> 00:19:53,839
That'll do.

376
00:20:08,480 --> 00:20:10,119
Red wine beef stew

377
00:20:10,720 --> 00:20:13,000
originated in Burgundy, France.

378
00:20:13,279 --> 00:20:13,880
There,

379
00:20:13,880 --> 00:20:16,799
they're famous for Pinot Noir red wine.

380
00:20:17,680 --> 00:20:18,440
Legend has it

381
00:20:18,640 --> 00:20:19,960
Burgundy farmers

382
00:20:19,960 --> 00:20:22,240
after a hard day's work

383
00:20:22,640 --> 00:20:24,440
would buy cheaper,

384
00:20:24,440 --> 00:20:26,440
tougher cuts of beef

385
00:20:26,440 --> 00:20:28,359
that are harder to cook.

386
00:20:28,920 --> 00:20:32,480
They'd slow-cook them in local red wine

387
00:20:33,119 --> 00:20:34,559
until the beef turned tender.

388
00:20:35,599 --> 00:20:38,359
The wine gives the beef a unique flavor.

389
00:20:39,599 --> 00:20:41,039
Snow falls outside,

390
00:20:41,400 --> 00:20:43,880
while the family gathers inside,

391
00:20:44,319 --> 00:20:48,559
enjoying a rich, comforting dinner.

392
00:21:23,160 --> 00:21:26,240
They'd add root vegetables

393
00:21:26,640 --> 00:21:29,839
to soak up the hearty gravy.

394
00:21:32,039 --> 00:21:33,599
Over time,

395
00:21:33,920 --> 00:21:36,200
this affordable, tasty dish

396
00:21:36,400 --> 00:21:39,680
became popular across France.

397
00:23:16,240 --> 00:23:19,440
But what made it loved worldwide

398
00:23:19,680 --> 00:23:22,319
was an American TV chef—

399
00:23:22,759 --> 00:23:24,319
Julia Child.

400
00:23:28,400 --> 00:23:29,640
I first learned about it

401
00:23:29,640 --> 00:23:31,839
from my favorite actress

402
00:23:32,279 --> 00:23:34,559
Meryl Streep's biopic

403
00:23:34,960 --> 00:23:36,559
Julie & Julia.

404
00:23:37,640 --> 00:23:38,880
Julie, an office worker,

405
00:23:38,880 --> 00:23:41,920
struggles with a fast-paced, unrewarding job.

406
00:23:42,359 --> 00:23:44,640
Her kitchen becomes her only escape.

407
00:23:45,279 --> 00:23:46,839
With her husband's support,

408
00:23:46,839 --> 00:23:49,039
she decides to spend a year

409
00:23:49,279 --> 00:23:53,039
cooking every recipe from Julia's book.

410
00:23:53,440 --> 00:23:54,920
She starts a blog

411
00:23:55,160 --> 00:23:56,960
to document her daily progress.

412
00:23:58,000 --> 00:24:00,279
She hopes that through cooking

413
00:24:00,720 --> 00:24:02,519
she'll find her true self

414
00:24:02,880 --> 00:24:05,160
and rediscover her love for life.

415
00:24:06,759 --> 00:24:09,039
There's a line in the film

416
00:24:09,720 --> 00:24:12,799
